{"title_page": "Neer dosa", "text_new": "{{Multiple issues|\n{{unreliable sources|date=July 2017}}\n{{original research|date=August 2017}}\n}}\n\n{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2017}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=February 2017}}\n{{Infobox prepared food\n| name             = \n| image            = Neer-dosa.jpg\n| image_size       = 270px\n| country          = [[India]]\n| region           = [[Tulunadu]]\n| type             = [[Dosa]]\n| main_ingredient  = [[Rice]]\n}}\n'''Neer dosa''' literally meaning '''water dosa''' in [[kannada language]], is a [[cr\u00eape]] prepared from [[rice]] [[Batter (cooking)|batter]]. Neer dosa is a delicacy from [[Tulu Nadu]] region and part of [[Mangalorean cuisine|Udupi - Mangalorean cuisine]].<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ylCqCgAAQBAJ&lpg=PA3&dq=neer%20dosa&pg=PA7#v=onepage&q=neer%20dosa&f=false|title=So Tasty Healthy Low Calorie Vegetarian Cooking Book-2: Take care calorie by calorie DOSAS AND SOUTH INDIAN MOUTH WATERING VARIETIES|last=S|first=Latha Maheswari|date=2015-10-03|publisher=AB Publishing House|isbn=9781517632694|language=en}}</ref><ref name=\":0\">{{Cite news|url=http://vegrecipesofkarnataka.com/6-neer-dosa.php|title=Neer dose Recipe {{!}} How to make neer dosa {{!}} Bari akki dose recipe {{!}} Neer dosa recipe|access-date=2016-12-03}}</ref><ref name=\":2\" />\n\n==Overview==\n''Neer'' is the word for water in [[Tulu language|Tulu]] language.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.archanaskitchen.com/magalorean-neer-dosa-recipe-savory-rice-coconut-crepe|title=Magalorean Neer Dosa Recipe (Savory Rice & Coconut Crepe)|last=Doshi|first=Archana|newspaper=Archana's Kitchen|access-date=2016-12-03}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.whiskaffair.com/neer-dosa|title=Mangalorean Neer Dosa Recipe|last=Affair|first=Whisk|newspaper=whisk affair|access-date=2018-10-03}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.sailusfood.com/2014/07/15/neer-dosa-recipe/|title=\ud83c\udf72Neer Dosa Recipe - How to make Neer Dosa with chicken curry|date=2014-07-15|website=Indian food recipes - Food and cooking blog|access-date=2016-12-03}}</ref>\n\nUnlike other [[dosa]]s neer dosa is known for its simple preparation method and lack of [[fermentation]]. Usually neer dosa is served with [[coconut chutney]], [[Sambar (dish)|sambar]], saagu and non vegetarian curries like chicken, mutton, fish and egg curry.\n\n== Ingredients ==\nEven though many variations exist for Neer Dosa batter, the two basic ingredients common to all of them are just soaked rice (or [[rice flour]]) and little [[salt]].<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.sailusfood.com/2014/07/15/neer-dosa-recipe/|title=\ud83c\udf72Neer Dosa Recipe - How to make Neer Dosa with chicken curry|date=2014-07-15|website=Indian food recipes - Food and cooking blog|access-date=2016-12-03}}</ref>{{better source|date=August 2017}}\n\n== Preparation ==\nThere is no requirement for fermentation of the [[rice]] in order to prepare Neer dosa. The rice needs to be soaked for at least 2 hours. After a quick wash and a drain the rice needs to be ground by adding water in order to get very fine batter. Additional amount of water can be added based on the thickness of the batter and then salt is added for taste. Finally the batter is used to prepare the dosa.<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=3m6DBAAAQBAJ&lpg=PT38&dq=neer%20dosa%20preparation&pg=PT39#v=onepage&q=neer%20dosa%20preparation&f=false|title=South Indian Cooking|last=Dalal|first=Tarla|publisher=Sanjay & Co|isbn=9788189491796|language=en}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of Indian breads]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{commons category inline|Neer dosa}}\n\n{{Indian bread}}\n{{Pancakes}}\n\n[[Category:Indian breads]]\n[[Category:Karnataka cuisine]]\n[[Category:Culture of Karnataka]]\n[[Category:Mangalorean cuisine]]\n[[Category:Tulu Nadu]]\n[[Category:Dosa]]\n", "text_old": "{{Multiple issues|\n{{unreliable sources|date=July 2017}}\n{{original research|date=August 2017}}\n}}\n\n{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2017}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=February 2017}}\n{{Infobox prepared food\n| name             = \n| image            = Neer-dosa.jpg\n| image_size       = 270px\n| country          = [[India]]\n| region           = [[Tulunadu]]\n| type             = [[Dosa]]\n| main_ingredient  = [[Rice]]\n}}\n'''Neer dosa''' literally meaning '''water dosa''' in [[Tulu language]], is a [[cr\u00eape]] prepared from [[rice]] [[Batter (cooking)|batter]]. Neer dosa is a delicacy from [[Tulu Nadu]] region and part of [[Mangalorean cuisine|Udupi - Mangalorean cuisine]].<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ylCqCgAAQBAJ&lpg=PA3&dq=neer%20dosa&pg=PA7#v=onepage&q=neer%20dosa&f=false|title=So Tasty Healthy Low Calorie Vegetarian Cooking Book-2: Take care calorie by calorie DOSAS AND SOUTH INDIAN MOUTH WATERING VARIETIES|last=S|first=Latha Maheswari|date=2015-10-03|publisher=AB Publishing House|isbn=9781517632694|language=en}}</ref><ref name=\":0\">{{Cite news|url=http://vegrecipesofkarnataka.com/6-neer-dosa.php|title=Neer dose Recipe {{!}} How to make neer dosa {{!}} Bari akki dose recipe {{!}} Neer dosa recipe|access-date=2016-12-03}}</ref><ref name=\":2\" />\n\n==Overview==\n''Neer'' is the word for water in [[Tulu language|Tulu]] language.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.archanaskitchen.com/magalorean-neer-dosa-recipe-savory-rice-coconut-crepe|title=Magalorean Neer Dosa Recipe (Savory Rice & Coconut Crepe)|last=Doshi|first=Archana|newspaper=Archana's Kitchen|access-date=2016-12-03}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.whiskaffair.com/neer-dosa|title=Mangalorean Neer Dosa Recipe|last=Affair|first=Whisk|newspaper=whisk affair|access-date=2018-10-03}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.sailusfood.com/2014/07/15/neer-dosa-recipe/|title=\ud83c\udf72Neer Dosa Recipe - How to make Neer Dosa with chicken curry|date=2014-07-15|website=Indian food recipes - Food and cooking blog|access-date=2016-12-03}}</ref>\n\nUnlike other [[dosa]]s neer dosa is known for its simple preparation method and lack of [[fermentation]]. Usually neer dosa is served with [[coconut chutney]], [[Sambar (dish)|sambar]], saagu and non vegetarian curries like chicken, mutton, fish and egg curry.\n\n== Ingredients ==\nEven though many variations exist for Neer Dosa batter, the two basic ingredients common to all of them are just soaked rice (or [[rice flour]]) and little [[salt]].<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.sailusfood.com/2014/07/15/neer-dosa-recipe/|title=\ud83c\udf72Neer Dosa Recipe - How to make Neer Dosa with chicken curry|date=2014-07-15|website=Indian food recipes - Food and cooking blog|access-date=2016-12-03}}</ref>{{better source|date=August 2017}}\n\n== Preparation ==\nThere is no requirement for fermentation of the [[rice]] in order to prepare Neer dosa. The rice needs to be soaked for at least 2 hours. After a quick wash and a drain the rice needs to be ground by adding water in order to get very fine batter. Additional amount of water can be added based on the thickness of the batter and then salt is added for taste. Finally the batter is used to prepare the dosa.<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=3m6DBAAAQBAJ&lpg=PT38&dq=neer%20dosa%20preparation&pg=PT39#v=onepage&q=neer%20dosa%20preparation&f=false|title=South Indian Cooking|last=Dalal|first=Tarla|publisher=Sanjay & Co|isbn=9788189491796|language=en}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of Indian breads]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{commons category inline|Neer dosa}}\n\n{{Indian bread}}\n{{Pancakes}}\n\n[[Category:Indian breads]]\n[[Category:Karnataka cuisine]]\n[[Category:Culture of Karnataka]]\n[[Category:Mangalorean cuisine]]\n[[Category:Tulu Nadu]]\n[[Category:Dosa]]\n", "name_user": "203.192.236.55", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Neer_dosa"}
